The paper analyzes big data sets from online social networking systems and proposes a model for meme popularity growth. The paper incorporates biological principles and human interest dynamics into the model. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper involves modeling and simulation, which suggests the sub-categories cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as likely options. Finally, the paper discusses optimization and control of OSN systems, which could fall under the sub-category cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
